ia-Hungary for the Establishment of International Copyright (Vienna, 24 April 1893). ATS 8 of 1901."] Australasian Legal Information Institute, Australian Treaty Series. Retrieved on 15 April 2017</ref> *1898 – Convention between the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland and Costa Rica for the Reciprocal Protection of Trade Marks, etc. (Guatemala, 5 March 1898)<ref> [http://www3.austlii.edu.au/au/other/dfat/treaties/1901/22.html "Convention between the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland and Costa Rica for the Reciprocal Protection of Trade Marks, etc (Guatemala, 5 March 1898)"] Australasian Legal Information Institute, Australian Treaty Series. Retrieved on 15 April 2017</ref> *1898 – Convention between the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland and Guatemala relative to Trade Marks (Guatemala, 20 July 1898)<ref>[http://www3.austlii.edu.au/au/other/dfat/treaties/1901/57.html "Convention between the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland and Guatemala relative to Trade Marks (Guatemala, 20 July 1898). ATS 57 of 1901."] Australasian Legal Information Institute, Australian Treaty Series. Retrieved on 15 April 2017</ref> *1949 – Exchange of Notes constituting an Agreement between the Government of Australia and the Government of the United States of America for the Extension of Time for Copyright<ref>[http://www3.austlii.edu.au/au/other/dfat/treaties/1949/17.html "Exchange of Notes constituting an Agreement between the Government of Australia and the Government of the United States of America for the Extension of Time for Copyright. ATS 17 of 1949."] Australasian Legal Information Institute, Australian Treaty Series. Retrieved on 15 April 2017</ref> *1955 – Exchange of Notes constituting an Agreement between the Government of Australia and the Government of the Republic of China [Taiwan] regarding the Reciprocal Protection of Inventions and Trade Marks<ref>[http://www3.austlii.edu.au/au/other/dfat/treaties/1955/1.html "Exchange of Notes constitu