{{Infobox artwork |image_file=Giovanni Paolo Panini – Modern Rome.jpg |title=Modern Rome |artist= Giovanni Paolo Panini |year=1757 |medium=[[Oil painting|Oil on canvas]] |height_metric=172.1 |width_metric=233 |height_imperial={{frac|67|3|4}} |width_imperial={{frac|91|3|4}} |metric_unit=cm |imperial_unit=in |city=[[Boston]] |museum=[[Museum of Fine Arts, Boston|Museum of Fine Art]] }} '''''Picture Gallery with Views of Modern Rome'''''<ref name="mfa.org">http://www.mfa.org/collections/object/picture-gallery-with-views-of-modern-rome-34215</ref> or simply '''''Modern Rome''''' is a 1757 painting by [[Italy|Italian]] artist [[Giovanni Paolo Panini]]. The original painting shows the arrangement of paintings originally commissioned by [[Étienne François, Count of Stainville]], later the Duke de Choiseul. He was the ambassador to [[Rome]] from between 1753 and 1757. The Duke is seated on an armchair, in the painting. Panini created three different versions of this painting.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=https://www.metmuseum.org/art/collection/search/437245|title=Giovanni Paolo Panini {{!}} Modern Rome {{!}} The Met|website=The Metropolitan Museum of Art, i.e. The Met Museum|access-date=2017-10-20}}</ref>
The picture gallery consists of a large number of paintings of buildings, monuments, and sculptures in Rome during the time that Panini painted it.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.tripimprover.com/blog/modern-rome-by-giovanni-paolo-panini|title=A discussion of Modern Rome by Panini|website=TripImprover - Get more out of your museum visits!|access-date=2017-10-20}}</ref> On the left side of this work are, among others, paintings of [[St. Peter's Basilica]], the [[Trevi Fountain]], and the [[Spanish Steps]]. On the right side are, among others, paintings of the church of [[Basilica di Santa Maria Maggiore|Santa Maria Maggiore]], the [[Piazza Navona]], and [[Villa Aldobrandini]]. In the middle are four statues, which are from front to back, the [[Medici lions|Medici lion]], [[Michelangelo]]'s ''[[Michelangelo|Moses]]'', [[Bernini]]'s statue of ''[[Bernini|David]]'', and Bernini's statue of ''[[Apollo and Daphne (Bernini)|Apollo and Daphne]]''.<ref name=":0" /> The painting is the pendant to Panini's ''[[Ancient Rome (painting)|Ancient Rome]]'' painting.<ref name="mfa.org"/>
